132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 461
S.P. 194 In Senate, February 11, 2025
An Act to Fund Rural Patrol Services in Washington County
(EMERGENCY)
Received by the Secretary of the Senate on February 5, 2025. Referred to the Committee
on Criminal Justice and Public Safety pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator MOORE of Washington.
Cosponsored by Representative MINGO of Calais and
Representatives: DANA of the Passamaquoddy Tribe, FAULKINGHAM of Winter Harbor,
MCINTYRE of Lowell, QUINT of Hodgdon, STROUT of Harrington, TUELL of East
Machias.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Emergency preamble. Whereas, acts and resolves of the Legislature do not
2 become effective until 90 days after adjournment unless enacted as emergencies; and
3 Whereas, this legislation must take effect before the expiration of the 90-day period
4 to address as soon as possible the potential public safety issues presented by the reduction
5 of rural patrols by the Maine State Police; and
6 Whereas, in the judgment of the Legislature, these facts create an emergency within
7 the meaning of the Constitution of Maine and require the following legislation as
8 immediately necessary for the preservation of the public peace, health and safety; now,
9 therefore,
10 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
11 Sec. 1. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
12 allocations are made.
13 PUBLIC SAFETY, DEPARTMENT OF
14 State Police 0291
15 Initiative: Provides funding for 4 Maine State Trooper positions and related All Other to
16 conduct rural patrols in Washington County.
17 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
18 POSITIONS - LEGISLATIVE COUNT 4.000 4.000
